CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Teen-Queen Contestants - These fourteen young misses of the Hill District are vying for the title Teen-Queen in the annual contest sponsored by Hill City.  They are, left to right:...Anna Farmer and LaVerne Brown"
TitMainTitle: Two frames, portrait of Anna Farmer wearing light colored blouse with decorative yoke and ruffles, posed in front of a light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of LaVerne Brown wearing a dark sweater, posed in front of a light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest
